# Confidentiality blocklist — copy this file to `.githooks/patterns.local` and
# fill in your real, project-confidential exact terms. `patterns.local` is
# gitignored (matched by `*.local`) so the real terms never enter the repo.
#
# Format: one POSIX extended-regex (ERE) per line.
#   * Lines starting with `#` and blank lines are ignored.
#   * Each pattern is matched (grep -E) against every staged file's content.
#   * A match hard-fails the commit.
#
# Put here the terms that must never be committed to this public repo but that
# cannot be expressed as a generic structural pattern — e.g. competitor names,
# internal codenames, regulation acronyms, personal handles, private vault dirs.
#
# Examples (replace with your real terms — these are placeholders):
# \bAcmeCompetitor\b
# INTERNAL_CODENAME
# private-notes-vault
# REG_ACRONYM
